Rockaway Township Public Schools
August 12 at 4:47 PM ·

RTSD is connecting students and teachers safely with technology
Our technicians have spent the summer repairing and cleaning Chromebooks, and we'll continue to provide support and improvements as the year goes on.
We have implemented policies that help to ensure everyone gets equitable access to technology, and we are building an infrastructure that ensures kids can learn anywhere, anytime, safely.
At RTSD we're facing the future together!
#RTSDCleanTeam

shared_text:
Rockaway Township Public Schools
July 30 at 2:48 PM ·

RTSD is capable of rapidly sanitizing environments.
Above and beyond our rigorous daily cleaning measures,
we are using state of the art Electrostatic Spraying Systems.
These systems provide fast, efficient, and thorough coverage over a wide range of surfaces.

And the solution used in the sprayer (Bioseque Botanical Disinfectant)
Kills Norovirus in just 4 minutes as well as 99.99% of Viruses, Bacteria, Fungi, and Mold, while still being a botanically derived US EPA registered Biodegradable disinfectant containing no harmful chemicals, chlorine or phosphates.

RTSD will use these tools to disinfect all district locations regularly and as an immediate response to any potential outbreak, because the safety and security of our students and staff comes first.

#RTSDCleanTeam

shared_text:
Rockaway Township Public Schools
July 23 at 5:28 PM ·

RTSD is creating a safe bussing environment, because our students' safety comes first.
Both Students and Drivers will wear face masks while on the bus.
And the 1st student on the bus, is the last student off the bus.
RTSD will sanitize our busses before and after every bus route.
Come September we will be ready to bus our students safely.
#RTSDCleanTeam

post_text:
Dear Community,

This is an important announcement from the Rockaway Township School District.

In the event that there is a state mandated public-health related school closure, we are preparing our district for the potential to meet the needs of the community in implementing Online Instructional Days (OIDs).

In consideration of that planning we have three important announcements.

First, there will be an early Dismissal schedule for all schools on Monday, March 16th to allow for training and preparation of teachers and staff.

Second, please reach out to your child's Principal if your family is in need of a Chromebook, were online instruction to be needed from your home.

Lastly, please reach out to your child's Principal if your family is in need of access to the Internet, were online instruction to be needed from your home.

For more information regarding Online Instructional Days, please visit our webpage at www.rocktwp.net for more information.
